'''Ereneda''' or '''Most Revered Ereneda''' was one of the titles the [[Hapan]]s gave to their [[Queen Mother]], whether they were the incumbent Queen or had abdicated. In their native language, it meant ''she who has no equal''. It reflected how the Hapans almost worshiped their ruler.

